CONTRIBUTION POLICY
================================================================================

5. CONTRIBUTOR LICENSE AGREEMENT (CLA)
   To ensure full legal protection of the Creator's rights, contributors 
   may be required to sign a Contributor License Agreement (CLA). The CLA 
   reiterates and formalizes the terms of this license.
   
   For non-trivial contributions (more than 50 lines of code or significant 
   features), the Creator may request a formal CLA signature. Failure to 
   sign a requested CLA will result in the PR being closed without merge.

6. PULL REQUESTS & CONTRIBUTIONS
   By submitting a pull request, issue, or any contribution to the 
   HealthyPixels repository, you agree to:
   
   a) The ownership assignment terms in Section 2 above.
   
   b) That your Contribution is original work created by you and does not 
      infringe any third-party rights.
   
   c) That you have the legal right to assign these rights to the Creator.
   
   d) To sign a formal CLA if requested by the Creator.
   
   e) That the Creator may accept, modify, reject, or supersede any 
      Contribution at its sole discretion.

7. EMPLOYEE & CORPORATE CONTRIBUTIONS
   If you are contributing code created as part of your employment, or 
   you are employed by a corporation:
   
   a) You must secure written permission from your employer before 
      submitting contributions.
   
   b) Your employer may be required to sign a CLA.
   
   c) Contributions made without employer permission may be rejected and 
      result in legal liability.

